Hebei Establishes Buddhist Art Research Institute
SHIJIAZHUANG , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- The Zhendan Buddhist Art Research Institute , first of its kind in China , was established Sunday in Shijiazhuang , capital of north China 's Hebei Province .
Numerous relics show Buddhism 's over 2,000-year history in China .
Buddhism has , in fact , had a great influence on the nation 's politics , economy , culture and folk customs .
The institute will specialize in a variety of religious art and cultural forms of Buddhism , including literature , calligraphy , painting , sculpture , photography , handicrafts , architecture , music , opera and movies .
